# identifiers:
#   - type: doi
#     value: "10.5281/zenodo.XXXXXXX"
#     description: "Zenodo archive of release v1.0.0"
keywords:
  - "organic chemistry"
  - "chemical education"
  - "3D visualization"
  - "reaction mechanisms"
  - "stereochemistry"
  - "conformational analysis"
  - "interactive learning"
  - "WebGL"
  - "Three.js"
  - "AI-assisted development"
abstract: >-
  OC3D is a single-file, trilingual (German/English/French), browser-based
  learning environment for introductory organic chemistry. It provides 33
  didactically sequenced interactive 3D modules covering reaction mechanisms
  with synchronized energy profiles, conformational analysis, stereochemistry,
  electronic effects, and aromaticity. The application requires no
  installation and collects no user data.
